        {
            "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
            "body": "> I'll try to fix it at the source by preventing the msg buffer from being unloaded on tabpage close \r\n\r\nA manual repro to verify the fix:\r\n```lua\r\nlocal msg_timeout = 10000 \r\nlocal zq_delay = 3000 \r\n\r\nrequire('vim._core.ui2').enable({\r\n  msg = { target = 'msg', msg = { timeout = msg_timeout } },\r\n})\r\n\r\nvim.cmd('tabnew')\r\nvim.cmd('echo \"hello\"')\r\n\r\nvim.defer_fn(function()\r\n  vim.cmd('normal! ZQ')\r\nend, zq_delay)\r\n```\r\nRun with `nvim --clean -u repro.lua`.\r\nCurrent: after close the tabpage and `ZQ`, we would not see `hello` and got an error.\r\nExpected(after fix): `hello` remains visible and no error.\r\n\r\ncc @luukvbaal \r\n\r\n\r\n",
